{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}} {{spanish name|Sánchez|Mina}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Davinson Sánchez | image = FWC 2018 - Round of 16 - COL v ENG - D Sánchez.jpg | image_size = 200 | caption = Sánchez with [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] | fullname = Davinson Sánchez Mina<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur59820.html |title=Davinson Sanchez |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|6|12|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=FIFA World Cup Russia 2018: List of players: Colombia |publisher=FIFA |format=PDF |page=5 |date=15 July 2018 |accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Caloto, Cauca|Caloto]], Colombia | height = 1.87 m<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://english.ajax.nl/the-club/ajax-1-1/the-players/player.htm?dbpage=442504&dbid=15669&typeofpage=443474 |title=Davinson Sánchez – English |accessdate=27 July 2017 |website= |publisher=Ajax}}</ref> | position = [[Centre back]] | currentclub = [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] | clubnumber = 6 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2013–2016 | clubs1 = [[Atlético Nacional]] | caps1 = 26 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2016–2017 | clubs2 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] | caps2 = 32 | goals2 = 6 | clubs3 = [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] | caps3 = 49 | goals3 = 1 | years3 = 2017– | nationalyears1 = 2013 | nationalteam1 = [[Colombia national under-17 football team|Colombia U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 2 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2014–2015 | nationalteam2 = [[Colombia national under-20 football team|Colombia U20]] | nationalcaps2 = 14 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2016 | nationalteam3 = [[Colombia Olympic football team|Colombia Olympic]] | nationalcaps3 = 2 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | nationalyears4 = 2016– | nationalteam4 = [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] | nationalcaps4 = 18 | nationalgoals4 = 0 | pcupdate = 9 March 2019 (UTC) | ntupdate = 22 March 2019 (UTC) }} '''Davinson Sánchez Mina''' (born 12 June 1996) is a Colombian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre back]] for English {{English football updater|TottenhH}} club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] and for the [[Colombia national football team|Colombian national team]]. Sanchez is Tottenham's club record signing, costing them around £42 million.
==Club career== ===Atlético Nacional=== As a youth, Sánchez played in the youth academy of [[América de Cali]], but after his parents moved he transferred to [[Atlético Nacional]], where he was educated under the wings of [[Juan Carlos Osorio]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/colombia/2016/03/16/56e9b8ece2704e12048b4631.html |title=No hay título que se le resista a Davinson Sánchez |newspaper=Marca |location=Madrid |date=16 March 2016 |language=Spanish}}</ref> The defender made his debut for the senior team on 27 October 2013, in a 0–1 loss to [[Boyacá Chicó]]. Osorio put the player in the starting lineup and he completed the entire match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/10/27/colombia/primera-a/atletico-nacional/deportivo-boyaca-chico-futbol-club/1495421/ |title=Atlético Nacional vs. Boyacá Chicó |date=27 October 2013 |publisher=Soccerway}}</ref>
On 2 March 2016, Sánchez scored his first goal for Nacional in a 3–0 victory over [[Sporting Cristal]] from Peru in the [[Copa Libertadores]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/03/02/south-america/copa-libertadores/atletico-nacional/club-sporting-cristal/2185076/ |title=Atlético Nacional vs. Sporting Cristal |date=2 March 2016 |publisher=Soccerway}}</ref> Due to his performances for Nacional, foreign clubs including [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]], and [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] showed an interest in signing the player.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://torcedores.com/noticias/2016/05/mercado-da-bola-2016-flamengo-espera-anunciar-dois-zagueiros-e-um-atacante-nesta-semana |title=Mercado da bola 2016: Flamengo espera anunciar dois zagueiros e um atacante nesta semana |date=24 May 2016 |publisher=Torcedores |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccernews.nl/news/356520/Colombiaanse_centrale_verdediger_tekent_bij_Ajax_in_plaats_van_FC_Barcelona |title=Colombiaanse centrale verdediger tekent bij Ajax in plaats van FC Barcelona |publisher=SoccerNews.nl |language=Dutch |date=1 June 2016}}</ref> Barcelona made a formal offer to sign the player, but Sánchez declined the offer because he didn't want to start in [[FC Barcelona B]], the reserve team.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.voetbalzone.nl/doc.asp?uid=279065 |title=Barcelona loopt blauwtje: ‘Hij heeft daar geen enkele zekerheid |publisher=Voetbalzone |language=Dutch |date=27 May 2016}}</ref> He won the Copa Libertadores 2016 against Ecuadorian [[Independiente del Valle]].{{citation needed|date=December 2018}}
===Ajax=== In June 2016, Sánchez signed a five-year contract with Dutch side [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], until 2021.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ajax.nl/streams/ajax-actueel/ajax-contracteert-davinson-sanchez-mina.htm |title=Ajax contracteert Davinson Sánchez Mina |publisher=Ajax |language=Dutch |date=21 June 2016}}</ref> The club paid a transfer fee of €5&nbsp;million to Atlético Nacional.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegraaf.nl/telesport/voetbal/ajax/26034985/__Ajax_heeft_2e_Colombiaan_binnen__.html#voetbal/227/fixtures/ |title=Ajax heeft tweede Colombiaanse aanwinst binnen |newspaper=De Telegraaf |language=Dutch |date=19 June 2016}}</ref> A few days earlier, Ajax had signed Sánchez' compatriot [[Mateo Cassierra]], thus making him the second Colombian in the squad. Sánchez joined his new team after Nacional had finished its participation in the [[2016 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hsbnoticias.com/noticias/deportes/f%C3%BAtbol/oficial-atletico-nacional-cede-davinson-sanchez-al-ajax-pe-217299 |title=Oficial: Atlético Nacional cede a Davinson Sánchez al Ajax, pero jugará Copa Libertadores |publisher=HSB Noticias |date=21 June 2016 |language=Spanish}}</ref> Sánchez debuted with Ajax on 13 August in a 2–2 tie with [[Roda JC Kerkrade]], he started and played the 90 minutes. His first goal with the club was on 24 September against [[PEC Zwolle]]. On 8 May 2017, he was named as best player of the season for [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://colombiareports.com/colombia-defender-scoops-player-year-award-dutch-giants-ajax/ |title=Colombia's Davinson Sanchez ‘player of the year’ after 1st year at Dutch giants Ajax}}</ref>
===Tottenham Hotspur=== On 18 August 2017, [[Premier League]] club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] announced that they had agreed a move for Sánchez signing a six-year contract subject to a work permit, for a reported transfer fee of up to £42&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41031823 |title=Davinson Sanchez: Tottenham complete signing of Ajax defender on six-year deal |publisher=BBC Sport |date=23 August 2017 |accessdate=29 August 2017}}</ref> He made his debut on 27 August as a substitute for [[Mousa Dembélé (Belgian footballer)|Mousa Dembélé]] in the 92nd minute in a 1–1 draw with [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40990430 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 1 – 1 Burnley |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 August 2017 |accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref>
On 15 May 2018, Sánchez signed a new contract with Tottenham, keeping him at the club until 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/first-team/general/davinson-signs-new-contract-150518/ |title=Davinson signs new contract |date=15 May 2018 |accessdate=15 May 2018 |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.}}</ref>
On 10 February 2019, Sánchez scored his first goal for Tottenham in the Premier League game against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/02/10/tottenham-vs-leicester-premier-league-live-score-latest-updates/ |title=Spurs hold on to beat profligate Leicester after Jamie Vardy misses penalty with first touch |date=10 February 2019 |first1=Jeremy |last1=Wilson|first2= Alistair |last2=Tweedale, |accessdate=10 February 2019 |publisher=The Telegraph}}</ref>
==International career== [[José Pékerman]] called up Sánchez for a training squad with the senior [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] squad in February 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.oximity.com/article/Pekerman-calls-up-local-players-with-a-1 |title=Pekerman calls-up local players with a view to WC qualifying |publisher=oximity.com |date=12 February 2016 |accessdate=11 July 2016}}</ref>
In May 2018 he was named in Colombia's preliminary 35-man [[Colombia national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb |title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – Final 23-man lists {{!}} Goal.com|access-date=5 June 2018}}</ref>
In June 2018 he was named in Colombia's final 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/colombia/story/3517715/colombia-name-world-cup-squad;-radamel-falcaojames-rodriguez-feature |title=Colombia name World Cup squad |publisher=ESPN|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref> He played in all three group matches and their round of 16 match.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/team/results/_/id/208/colombia |title=Colombia Results – 2018–19 {{!}} ESPN|publisher=ESPN|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref>
