{{Infobox football biography | name = Juan Foyth | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Juan Marcos Foyth<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/465277 |title=Squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2017 |accessdate=9 September 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|01|12|df=y}} | birth_place = [[La Plata]], Argentina | height = 1.79 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/25309/Juan-Foyth/overview |title=Juan Foyth: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=11 November 2018}}</ref> | currentclub = [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] | clubnumber = 21 | position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre-back]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes]] | years1 = 2017 | clubs1 = [[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes]] | caps1 = 7 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2017– | clubs2 = [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] | caps2 = 8 | goals2 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2017 | nationalteam1 = [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina U20]] | nationalcaps1 = 12 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2018– | nationalteam2 = [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] | nationalcaps2 = 1 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | club-update = 08:00, 24 February 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 19 November 2018 }} '''Juan Marcos Foyth''' (born 12 January 1998) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] player who plays as [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for English club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] and the [[Argentina national football team]].<ref name="auto">{{cite web |url=http://www.planetfootball.com/quick-reads/spurs-target-juan-foyth-good-football-manager/ |title=Who is Spurs target Juan Foyth and is he any good on Football Manager?}}</ref>
==Club career== ===Estudiantes de La Plata=== Foyth started playing for a number of years in the Youth academy, initially as an attacking midfielder, then moved to a central defender position before he turned 16.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/meet-juan-foyth-tottenhams-new-stopper-told-coaches-who-helped-him-get-here |title=Meet Juan Foyth: Tottenham's new stopper, as told by the coaches who helped him get there |first=Peter |last=Coates |date=19 September 2017 |work=Four Four Two}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract in January 2017, which linked him to the club until June 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=First contract for Juan Marcos Foyth |url=http://www.estudiantesdelaplata.com/en/primer-contrato-para-juan-marcos-foyth/ |website=estudiantesdelaplata.com |publisher=Estudiantes de la Plata |accessdate=30 August 2017 |date=9 January 2017}}</ref> He made his Primera Division debut on 19 March 2017 against [[Club Atlético Patronato|Patronato]] aged 19.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2017/07/29/scout-report-juan-foyth-estudiantes-ball-playing-defender/ |title=Scout Report: Juan Foyth |first=Kaustubh |last=Pandey |work=Outside of the Boot |date=29 July 2017}}</ref> He went on to play a further six times in the league, with additional two appearances in the Copa Sudamericana.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dxtv.gob.ar/noticias/juan-foyth-fue-presentado-como-jugador-del-tottenham_3367#sthash.338spTjO.dpbs |title=Juan Foyth fue presentado como jugador del Tottenham |date=30 August 2017 |work=Deportv}}</ref>
===Tottenham Hotspur=== Foyth joined [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] for a reported £8m on 30 August 2017 on a five-year contract until 2022.<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/juan-foyth-completes-move-300817/ |title=Foyth completes move |date=30 August 2017|access-date=30 August 2017 |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41100066 |title=Juan Foyth: Tottenham sign Estudiantes centre-back on five-year deal |date=20 August 2017 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 19 September 2017 in an [[2017–18 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] tie against [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] that Tottenham won 1–0.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-1-barnsley-0-maurico-pochettino-lauds-juan-foyth-after-impressive-wembley-debut-a3638816.html |title=Tottenham 1 Barnsley 0: Maurico Pochettino lauds Juan Foyth after impressive Wembley debut |first=Jack |last=Rosser |work=Evening Standard |date=19 September 2017}}</ref> He made his league debut for the club on 3 November 2018 in a 3–2 away win against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], where he conceded two penalties which were both converted.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46000540 |title=Spurs survive Wolves fightback to go fourth |work=BBC Sport |date=3 November 2018}}</ref> In his next Premier League appearance, an away match against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], he scored his first career goal, handing Tottenham a 1–0 win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/nov/10/crystal-palace-tottenham-premier-league-report |title=Juan Foyth scores first career goal to give Tottenham win at Crystal Palace |first=Paul |last=MacInnes |date=10 November 2018 |work=The Guardian}}</ref>
==International career== Foyth was born in Argentina, is of Polish descent and holds a Polish passport.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2017/juan-foyth-set-to-complete-move-to-psg/|title=Juan Foyth set to complete move to PSG - Get French Football News|website=www.getfootballnewsfrance.com}}</ref>
Foyth played for the [[Argentina national under-20 football team]]. In 2017, he made 12 appearances for the national youth team: nine at the [[2017 South American Youth Football Championship]] in Ecuador, and another three during the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup]].<ref name="auto"/>
Foyth received his first call-up to the senior [[Argentina national football team]] for a number of friendly games to be played in October 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://cartilagefreecaptain.sbnation.com/2018/9/28/17913872/tottenham-hotspur-juan-foyth-international-argentina-first-call-up-2018 |title=Tottenham’s Juan Foyth named to Argentina squad for upcoming friendlies |first=Dustin |last=Menno |date=28 September 2018 |work=Cartilage Free Captain}}</ref> He made his actual debut on 16 November 2018 in a friendly against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] where he helped Argentina to a 2–0 win. He won the [[man of the match]] award and received wide praise for his performance in this match.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2018/11/19/argentine-press-rave-about-tottenham-hotspur-star-juan-foyth/ |title=Argentine press rave about Tottenham Hotspur star Juan Foyth |first=Dan|last= Coombs|work=HITC |date=19 November 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.101greatgoals.com/news/tottenham-hotspurs-juan-foyth-lauded-following-argentina-2-0-mexico/ |title=Tottenham Hotspur’s Juan Foyth lauded following Argentina 2-0 Mexico |first=Jamie |last=Brown |date= November 17, 2018 |work=101 Great Goals }}</ref>
